HEADWORD: Ten-pounder
<hw>Ten"-pound`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large oceanic fish (<spn>Elops saurus</spn>) found in the
tropical parts of all the oceans. It is used chiefly for bait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

